		<li class="comment byuser comment-author-bi-monkey bypostauthor odd alt thread-odd thread-alt depth-1" id="comment-12314">
				<div id="div-comment-12314" class="comment-body">
				<div class="comment-author vcard">
			<img alt='' src='http://0.gravatar.com/avatar/22ea2eabbe63e4fce4ba04701e33c0e6?s=48&amp;d=http%3A%2F%2F0.gravatar.com%2Favatar%2Fad516503a11cd5ca435acc9bb6523536%3Fs%3D48&amp;r=G' class='avatar avatar-48 photo' height='48' width='48' />			<cite class="fn"><a href='http://www.bimonkey.com' rel='external nofollow' class='url'>BI Monkey</a></cite> <span class="says">says:</span>		</div>
		
		<div class="comment-meta commentmetadata"><a href="http://www.bimonkey.com/2009/06/the-pivot-transformation/comment-page-1/#comment-12314">
			September 22, 2011 at 12:54 pm</a>		</div>

		<p>Hi Srinivas </p>
<p>Unfortunately the Pivot component cannot handle changing keys &#8211; there&#8217;s no way to dynamically allow for new Pivot Keys. </p>
<p>The only workaround I can think of is to use surrogate keys for your values, so you pivot on values 1 to 20 (or however many you think you will need). That way you can set up the component for a bigger range of values than you currently have without having to worry about what those values actually are.</p>

		<div class="reply">
					</div>
				</div>
		</li><!-- #comment-## -->
		<li class="comment even thread-even depth-1" id="comment-13096">
				<div id="div-comment-13096" class="comment-body">
				<div class="comment-author vcard">
			<img alt='' src='http://0.gravatar.com/avatar/af81f4cb6f3173a59e9fec3878f5ab9b?s=48&amp;d=http%3A%2F%2F0.gravatar.com%2Favatar%2Fad516503a11cd5ca435acc9bb6523536%3Fs%3D48&amp;r=G' class='avatar avatar-48 photo' height='48' width='48' />			<cite class="fn">Steve Francis</cite> <span class="says">says:</span>		</div>
		
